Baoxing afforestation project (hereafter refer to as “the project”) is located in Baoxing County, Ya’an City, Sichuan Province of China, where in 1869, the world’s first giant panda was discovered, and named as the hometown of the giant panda.
Based on the principle of matching sites with tree species, the project aims to plant native tree species of Cryptomeria, Phellodendron Chinese schneid, Magnolia officinalis, Alnuscremastogyne, with a simple tree species or mixed tree species on barren lands in 9 township of Baoxing County without clearing the sparse shrub in the barren lands, with area of 4,467.98ha (67,019.7 Mu )since 2016, all the lands for afforestation activities belong to the villagers and the village committees manage the lands on behalf of villagers. Sichuan Jiajinshan Forestry Bureau (hereafter referred to as Jiajinshan) has been fully authorized by all the village committees to act as the project proponent to implement project management and monitoring, etc. 
The implementation of the project is expected to increase the forest coverage and its photosynthesis, and is expected to increase the GHG emission removals.
Prior to the project implementation, all the project sites are barren lands, without its implementation, all the sites will keep the same circumstances with no natural renewal and reforestation.
The implementation of the project is expected to generate GHG emissions removals of 4,708,622tCO2e within 27 years’ crediting period, and the expected annual average GHG emission removals is156,954tCO2e.

The project aims to: 
- Improve the forest coverage, remove greenhouse gas and mitigate climate change; 
- Enhance biodiversity conservation by increasing the connectivity of forests which is critical for wildlife;
- Improve soil and water conservation in the low and middle mountainous area; 
-Generate income and job opportunities for local communities and villagers as well as training opportunities.

